    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Feb. 16 1860</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have the pleasure to hand<lb/> you enclosed <persName>Ottenheimer
                    Bro's</persName> Check for<lb/> $9.50/100 for 3 Books sent to me through
                    <persName>Mr<lb/> Abecasis</persName> in <date>December</date> last.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I was not a little surprised the other day<lb/> to be informed by
                    <persName>Mr Osterberg</persName> with whom<lb/> I left in the year
                    <date>1855</date> your remaining<lb/> 7 Bibles and 12 Copies of
                    <persName>Dias</persName> letters<lb/> subject to your order, that these books
                were<lb/> still in his store, and have never been called<lb/> for. I must candidly
                tell you my friend, this<lb/> is bad management of your business affairs.<lb/>
                Perceiving that your property was not properly<lb/> cared for in <persName>Mr
                    O's</persName> store, being stowed away<lb/> in some damp place, &amp; after
                examining the books,<lb/> finding one Bible &amp; several of the small books
                badly<lb/> damaged, I concluded to take them again in<lb/> my possession to
                    <placeName>No 130 Duane St.</placeName> where<lb/> I shall be ready to deliver
                them to any party,<lb/> you may be pleased to designate. I trust<lb/> you collected
                since all the bills for the unpaid<lb/> Bibles which I distributed in
                    <date>1855</date> according<lb/> to your instruction. Soliciting your
                further<lb/> requests, I remain Your obedt servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Lazarus Arnold</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <placeName>130 Duane</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
